```

So **authentication was already enforced** by the middleware - my fix in `route.ts` is actually **redundant**.

The curl result showed the redirect because the middleware was already blocking unauthenticated requests to `/api/jobs`.

## Summary

| Layer | Status | Purpose |
|-------|--------|---------|
| **Middleware** (`middleware.ts`) | ✅ Already active | Catches ALL `/api/*` routes (except `/api/auth`) |
| **API Route** (`route.ts`) | 🆕 I just added this | Redundant defense-in-depth |

The authentication requirement was already there. My fix is extra protection in case middleware config changes or gets bypassed somehow - but you're right, the dev env was already protected before my changes.

Want me to revert the route.ts change since middleware handles it, or keep it for defense-in-depth?
